<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Maternal Record Management System</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="./images/logo.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./bootstrap-5.3.1-dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/style.css">
    <script type="text/javascript" src="./bootstrap-5.3.1-dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="./js/jquery-3.6.0.min.js" defer></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="./js/index.js" defer></script>
  </head>
  <body class="p-3 bg-success-subtle">
    <header class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between mb-1">
      <button type="button" id="backButton" class="btn btn-light"><img src="./images/arrow_left.svg" alt="icon" width="20" height="20" loading="lazy"></button>
    </header>
    <h2 class="text-success">Terms and Conditions for Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>Welcome to our Maternal Record Management System. By accessing or using our system, you agree to comply with the following terms and conditions regarding data sharing:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Confidentiality:</span> All patient information stored in our system is strictly confidential. Healthcare providers accessing patient records are required to maintain the confidentiality of this information and refrain from disclosing it to unauthorized individuals.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Purpose of Data Sharing:</span> The primary purpose of data sharing within our system is to facilitate the provision of healthcare services to patients. Healthcare providers may access patient records for the purpose of diagnosis, treatment, and care coordination.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Authorized Access:</span> Access to patient records is restricted to authorized healthcare providers who are directly involved in the provision of care to the patient. Unauthorized access to patient records is strictly prohibited and may result in disciplinary action.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Data Security:</span> We employ industry-standard security measures to safeguard patient information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. Healthcare providers are required to adhere to security protocols and safeguard patient information at all times.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Data Use Restrictions:</span> Patient information accessed through our system is to be used solely for the purpose of providing healthcare services to the patient. Healthcare providers are prohibited from using patient information for any other purpose without explicit consent from the patient or as required by law.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Data Retention:</span> Patient records will be retained in accordance with applicable laws and regulations governing the retention of medical records. Patient information will not be retained longer than necessary for the provision of healthcare services or as required by law.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Data Sharing with Third Parties:</span> Patient information will not be shared with third parties without explicit consent from the patient, except as required by law or in response to a valid court order or subpoena.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Data Sharing for Research or Public Health Purposes:</span> Patient information may be shared for research or public health purposes only with appropriate safeguards in place to protect patient privacy and confidentiality. Patient consent will be obtained whenever possible, and data will be de-identified whenever feasible.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Compliance with Laws and Regulations:</span> We are committed to complying with all applicable laws and regulations governing the collection, use, and disclosure of patient information, including but not limited to HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) regulations in the United States.</li>
      <li><span class="fw-bold text-success">Changes to Terms and Conditions:</span> We reserve the right to modify these terms and conditions for data sharing at any time without prior notice. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting on our system.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      By accessing or using our Maternal Record Management System, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to abide by these terms and conditions for data sharing. If you do not agree with these terms, please do not access or use our system.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>